# Project Conventions

## Config-Driven Content

**All text content, contact info, and data must be in `config.json`** - never hardcoded in HTML.

### Required Pattern

```html
<!-- ❌ BAD - Hardcoded -->
<h2>צרו קשר</h2>
<a href="tel:050-6940292">050-6940292</a>

<!-- ✅ GOOD - Config-driven with data attributes -->
<h2 data-config="contact-title">צרו קשר</h2>
<a href="tel:050-6940292" data-config="phone">050-6940292</a>
```

### Config Structure

Store all content in `config.json`:
- `designer.*` - Phone, email, address, name
- `social.*` - WhatsApp, Instagram, Facebook URLs
- `projects.items[]` - Project data with id, title, description, images
- `projectGalleries.*` - Gallery-specific data per project

## Project Pages

Each project page (`project-*.html`) should:
1. Use `data-config` attributes for all text
2. Reference `config.json` for project-specific content via project ID
3. Share the same contact form logic as main page
4. Load content dynamically via `main.js`

## Contact Forms

Contact forms appear in:
- Main page contact section
- Project page bottom section  
- Project page lightbox sidebar

All forms use the same submission logic in `main.js` and send to `/api/contact`.

## File Naming

- Project pages: `project-{id}.html` where id matches `config.json` project ID
- Project images: `images/{project-folder}/` with descriptive names
